00:03:21.390 --> 00:03:23.280
Eyewitnesses and Survivors.

00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:27.000
They are longtime refugees
languishing in camps.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.740
They're soldiers whom
unemployed meeting

00:03:29.740 --> 00:03:32.470
for a smoke or idle conversation.

00:03:32.470 --> 00:03:37.920
They're elderly savoring a
bowl of soup in a soup kitchen.

00:03:37.920 --> 00:03:41.590
They're children whose
playground is a toxic dump.

00:03:41.590 --> 00:03:44.380
Unfortunately, past is prologue.

00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:49.840
And with today's parallels,
we see a lot of challenges.

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:55.680
And I think a lot of this
landscape will be familiar to you.

00:04:00.350 --> 00:04:02.830
We're talking about
a lost generation.

00:04:02.830 --> 00:04:08.800
We're talking about trauma,
corruption, security issues.

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:11.920
Justice, elusive justice.

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:13.940
This is 1989 Baghdad.

00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:17.570
This little fellow is along
the banks of the Tigris River.

00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:21.990
He's a beggar who's hustling a
foreign visitor with card tricks

00:04:21.990 --> 00:04:24.160 position:56%
and he was a rare sight at the time.

00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:29.500
But since the Gulf War, intra-Iraqi
fighting, countless insurgencies

00:04:29.500 --> 00:04:34.140 position:56%
and of course the ISIS assault on
Iraq's independence, such as it was,

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:37.510
the number of young
Iraqi beggars has soared.

00:04:37.510 --> 00:04:40.160
Traditionally pampered,
even insulated

00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:41.950
by protective Arab parents --

00:04:41.950 --> 00:04:44.300
and you find this all
over the Arab world.

00:04:44.300 --> 00:04:49.460
Children here and throughout
these conflict areas are peddling

00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:53.590
everything from cigarettes to sex.

00:04:53.590 --> 00:04:59.180
And it is an absolute 180-degree
difference in the prospect

00:04:59.180 --> 00:05:06.570
for children growing up in
conflict areas in the Middle East.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:12.000
These folks back from the
front, eight-year war with Iran,

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:17.270
these Iraqi men, are shopping for
wedding dresses for their intended.

00:05:17.270 --> 00:05:18.730
By now they've married.

00:05:18.730 --> 00:05:21.050
They've probably had
multiple children.

00:05:21.050 --> 00:05:24.250
And those children now,
if past is prologue,

00:05:24.250 --> 00:05:28.950
those children now are suffering
from the same kinds of difficulties

00:05:28.950 --> 00:05:31.640
that the beggar boy,
30 years earlier,

00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:35.370
20 years earlier, suffered from.

00:05:35.370 --> 00:05:40.160
Unaccompanied children are the
most tragic byproducts of conflict.

00:05:40.160 --> 00:05:42.620
And the most vulnerable, of course.

00:05:42.620 --> 00:05:46.980
These three are orphans who escaped
Vukovar, which is a Croatian town,

00:05:46.980 --> 00:05:50.530
emblematic of the massacres,
the mass graves

00:05:50.530 --> 00:05:54.880
and the widespread devastation
of post-war Yugoslavia.

00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:57.780
Raped, tortured, often
forced to watch

00:05:57.780 --> 00:06:04.150
as their own family members
endured this, victims were refugees

00:06:04.150 --> 00:06:07.640
and their lives only
became more complicated.

00:06:07.640 --> 00:06:14.590 position:56%
They languished in those UN camps
and other hastily constructed homes.

00:06:14.590 --> 00:06:16.990
And as we see today,
government agencies,

00:06:16.990 --> 00:06:21.070
international relief organizations
try to provide the basics.

00:06:21.070 --> 00:06:23.030
Food, health, housing.

00:06:23.030 --> 00:06:26.640
But those efforts fall
severely short of needs.

00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:30.470
In this instance, in Croatia,
the state radio devoted hours

00:06:30.470 --> 00:06:32.580
to desperate family
members who were calling

00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:36.250
out for their family
members on the air.

00:06:36.250 --> 00:06:39.990
And it was and remains crushing.

00:06:39.990 --> 00:06:42.300
This is a very familiar site.

00:06:42.300 --> 00:06:44.130
It is a refugee camp.

00:06:44.130 --> 00:06:48.040
This one in Macedonia right
near the Albanian border.

00:06:48.040 --> 00:06:54.720
This is just post-Kosovo,
part of Yugoslavia.

00:06:54.720 --> 00:07:01.080
These families lived in
horrendous conditions.

00:07:01.080 --> 00:07:06.000
This particular camp was built
on top of a toxic waste site

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:12.280
and had plastic sheeting put on top
of it and then soil on top of that.

00:07:12.280 --> 00:07:16.480
The toxicity leaked of course and
there were a lot of open sores

00:07:16.480 --> 00:07:20.690
and a lot of health issues among
the refugees living in these camps.

00:07:20.690 --> 00:07:26.000
So even the camps themselves
can create big, big problems.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:31.210
Forget about busting
out of the camps.

00:07:31.210 --> 00:07:35.870
This is a sheep herder, a
Palestinian sheep herder, 1983,

00:07:35.870 --> 00:07:38.520
ten years after the '73 war.

00:07:38.520 --> 00:07:43.820
He entered a world back then
that was profoundly impacted

00:07:43.820 --> 00:07:49.330
by the divide between Israel
and its Arab neighbors.

00:07:49.330 --> 00:07:53.630
Today, the majority of west
bank Arabs are youth, his age.

00:07:53.630 --> 00:08:00.700
And upward of 50% of the
population is under the age of 15.

00:08:00.700 --> 00:08:04.790
There is staggering unemployment
in this cohort, perhaps 30,

00:08:04.790 --> 00:08:07.710
maybe as high as 60% unemployment.

00:08:07.710 --> 00:08:10.090
The data swings wildly on this.

00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:13.020
But it is among the
highest in the world.

00:08:14.190 --> 00:08:17.500
These toy assault rifles
were dangling

00:08:17.500 --> 00:08:21.810
from an east Jerusalem
shop fairly recently.

00:08:21.810 --> 00:08:26.530
And they are marketed to five- and
six-year-old Palestinian girls.

00:08:26.530 --> 00:08:31.280
If past is prologue, and I
think this is a recurring theme

00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:37.560
in our daily lives, trying to
grapple with these just collections

00:08:37.560 --> 00:08:39.460
of strife all over the world.

00:08:39.460 --> 00:08:43.160
This is the kind of sort
of subliminal training

00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:46.440
that comes out of conflict.

00:08:46.440 --> 00:08:51.950
This is the end of the
Cold War, or is it?

00:08:51.950 --> 00:08:53.250
Some say no.

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.620
But the end of the Cold War
and the fall of communism,

00:08:55.620 --> 00:09:00.120 position:56%
at least the first fall, was a major
shredding of the command economy.

00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:03.090
And any kind of safety
net that caught folks

00:09:03.090 --> 00:09:05.490
who needed housing,
healthcare and food.

00:09:05.490 --> 00:09:09.090
Hardship really spared no one,
except for the privileged few,

00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:11.630
those who had protection.

00:09:11.630 --> 00:09:14.180
And this is a Russian woman.

00:09:14.180 --> 00:09:15.480
This is not a Russian Jew.

00:09:15.480 --> 00:09:19.560
This is a Russian woman
who has no medical care.

00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:20.860
She has no food.

00:09:20.860 --> 00:09:22.160
She needs money.

00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:24.770
She has no job and she needs
to look after her family.

00:09:24.770 --> 00:09:31.680
The aging suffer probably the
most in post-war societies.

00:09:31.680 --> 00:09:35.790
They're often shut out of services
or simply forgotten or ignored

00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:39.140
by those who have undergone
trauma themselves.

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:42.020
This group is very smartly dressed.

00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:45.200
They put on their Sunday best every
time they go to the soup kitchen.

00:09:45.200 --> 00:09:47.080
It's a famous one in Moscow.

00:09:47.080 --> 00:09:53.460
It's called Hama and some of these
patrons ride the very dangerous

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:56.940
metro in Russia in Moscow.

00:09:56.940 --> 00:10:00.830
They ride two hours each way
to get a hot meal each day.

00:10:00.830 --> 00:10:03.250
Their penchants of
course have shriveled.

00:10:03.250 --> 00:10:07.080
Government assistance has
vanished and fuel and food prices

00:10:07.080 --> 00:10:09.370
of course have gone
through the roof.

00:10:09.370 --> 00:10:12.910
This for them is just the
latest in a succession

00:10:12.910 --> 00:10:15.970
of horrors they have
suffered over many decades.

00:10:15.970 --> 00:10:17.270
I don't have to remind many

00:10:17.270 --> 00:10:20.360
in this group there were
pogroms, anti-Jewish pogroms.

00:10:20.360 --> 00:10:25.470
The Holocaust, the Gulag,
Stalin's forced labor camps.

00:10:25.470 --> 00:10:27.420
Refused immigration.

00:10:27.420 --> 00:10:28.740
Banishment to Siberia.

00:10:28.740 --> 00:10:30.690
Viscous anti-Semitic attacks.

00:10:30.690 --> 00:10:34.650
The wrath of skinheads,
the ellipsis, it goes on.

00:10:34.650 --> 00:10:38.920
Today the soup kitchen serves
hundreds of indigent Jews.

00:10:38.920 --> 00:10:42.820
Most of these people live in
isolated, decrepit apartments

00:10:42.820 --> 00:10:47.570
and houses, some with no
running water or heat.

00:10:47.570 --> 00:10:51.050
This is Srebenica.

00:10:51.050 --> 00:10:53.630
I was there last summer
with the Holocaust Museum.

00:10:53.630 --> 00:10:57.090
We were part of the delegation
observing the 20th anniversary

00:10:57.090 --> 00:11:01.450
of the commemoration of
the massacre in Srebenica,

00:11:01.450 --> 00:11:08.260
which is on the border
of Bosnia and Serbia.

00:11:08.260 --> 00:11:12.240
And it's a mountaintop place.

00:11:12.240 --> 00:11:15.650
It's really a remarkable
place to get to.

00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:20.080
Lots of nips and tucks
and big turns.

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:26.180
It's probably emblematic to most as
sustaining one of the most savage,

00:11:26.180 --> 00:11:29.740
most horrific assaults
of the Balkan Wars.

00:11:29.740 --> 00:11:33.230
This survivor is cradling
a child and a grandchild.

00:11:33.230 --> 00:11:36.630
And she is among the many
Muslim women who fled and lived

00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:44.690
in the forest on roots and leaves
and other nutrients she could find.

00:11:44.690 --> 00:11:48.030
The women came back
after this assault

00:11:48.030 --> 00:11:53.410
and they came back
obviously to destroyed houses.

00:11:53.410 --> 00:11:56.110
Their men, their boys were gone.

00:11:56.110 --> 00:11:57.770
Most of the girls were gone.

00:11:57.770 --> 00:11:59.680
The children were gone.

00:11:59.680 --> 00:12:02.620
Houses pockmarked by shells.

00:12:02.620 --> 00:12:06.900
Fields were laid with mines.

00:12:06.900 --> 00:12:12.880
Constant reminders of terror that
should have ended decades ago.

00:12:12.880 --> 00:12:15.800
But those things are
still very present.

00:12:15.800 --> 00:12:19.230
There are many, many swaths of
areas around Srebenica for example,

00:12:19.230 --> 00:12:22.750
and throughout the
Balkans that are minefields

00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:25.640
and difficult to traverse.

00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:30.000 position:56%
In Srebenica and throughout Bosnia,
Muslim women suffered enormous shame

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:33.560
when they were left with
babies born from sexual attack.

00:12:33.560 --> 00:12:40.190
This is a young woman in Guatemala,
where there is full-out gang war,

00:12:40.190 --> 00:12:41.990
as there is throughout
the northern triangle

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:44.780
in Honduras and El Salvador.

00:12:44.780 --> 00:12:49.450
This particular Central American
nation ranks among the worst

00:12:49.450 --> 00:12:51.270
and most violent countries.

00:12:51.270 --> 00:12:54.050
And women and girls are
the most vulnerable.

00:12:54.050 --> 00:12:57.370
They are under intense
pressure to marry.

00:12:57.370 --> 00:13:02.090
Legal age is 14 but they bear
children before they even really

00:13:02.090 --> 00:13:04.070
learn how to take care
of themselves.

00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:07.500
And it's something that is so --

00:13:07.500 --> 00:13:10.000
it's repeated so often
throughout the world.

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:15.820
I'm just giving you a little
snippet to think about.

00:13:15.820 --> 00:13:17.620
Slightly older.

00:13:17.620 --> 00:13:18.920
This is Nigeria.

00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:22.510
Like so many nations embroiled
in or emerging from conflict,

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.530
Nigerians are just strangled.

00:13:24.530 --> 00:13:26.730
They're strangled by corruption.

00:13:26.730 --> 00:13:28.310
They're strangled by fear.

00:13:28.310 --> 00:13:31.310
The country has huge debt
and crumbling infrastructure.

00:13:31.310 --> 00:13:34.280
Even as it pumps billions
of dollars' worth of oil.

00:13:34.280 --> 00:13:35.820
That's how corrupt it is.

00:13:35.820 --> 00:13:39.190 position:56%
More than two-thirds of the citizens
live below the poverty line.

00:13:39.190 --> 00:13:44.560
HIV/AIDS, the top killer,
is still quite vicious.

00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:47.990
And its staggering infection
rate is the third highest

00:13:47.990 --> 00:13:51.270
in the world behind
India and South Africa.

00:13:51.270 --> 00:13:53.330
These villagers have
no running water,

00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:55.750
no electricity, no telephones.

00:13:55.750 --> 00:14:00.760
And they have the only health
clinic in the area for 37 villages.

00:14:00.760 --> 00:14:04.140
That health clinic
has a plastic curtain

00:14:04.140 --> 00:14:07.000
with two rooms that are barren.

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:09.330
No drugs, no facility.

00:14:09.330 --> 00:14:15.990
The most naked feeling of course
for the women and the girls is

00:14:15.990 --> 00:14:19.200
that they're vulnerable to
the radical Islamic groups,

00:14:19.200 --> 00:14:22.630
especially Boko Haram who is
widely known for kidnapping

00:14:22.630 --> 00:14:28.170
and sexually enslaving girls, as
those cradled in this woman's arms.

00:14:28.170 --> 00:14:29.620
Gangs and opportunism.

00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:32.480
Well, this is Brazil
outside one of the favelas,

00:14:32.480 --> 00:14:37.160
which is these squatter
settlements and impoverished areas

00:14:37.160 --> 00:14:39.810
that line the big cities
in the country.

00:14:39.810 --> 00:14:43.840
There is full-out gang warfare
throughout this part of the world.

00:14:43.840 --> 00:14:50.080
And this gentleman has
been captured, happily so,

00:14:50.080 --> 00:14:53.150
into a work program
sponsored by an NGO.

00:14:53.150 --> 00:14:58.430
He's left the gang in
favor of a full-time job.

00:14:58.430 --> 00:15:02.510
And he's lugging a sack
of bottles for recycling.

00:15:02.510 --> 00:15:07.900
The gang war is just
gripping in El Salvador.

00:15:07.900 --> 00:15:10.580
This woman lost all of her boys.

00:15:10.580 --> 00:15:15.140
It's been over four years since
this gang truce in El Salvador.

00:15:15.140 --> 00:15:18.810
It's a broker deal designed to
reduce the number of killings.

00:15:18.810 --> 00:15:20.500
Not to reduce them all told.

00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:27.420
Just to reduce the numbers, in
exchange for prison transfers.

00:15:27.420 --> 00:15:30.660 position:56%
It's really hit the skids of course.

00:15:30.660 --> 00:15:34.740
This fellow is a young boy
whose mother commutes upwards

00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:39.590
of five hours a day round trip
for her work as a housekeeper

00:15:39.590 --> 00:15:41.890
for more well-to-do Salvadorans.

00:15:41.890 --> 00:15:45.350
He does not leave his
corrugated metal housing.

00:15:45.350 --> 00:15:46.710
Does not even go outside

00:15:46.710 --> 00:15:51.900
because gang members live
next door, across the street.

00:15:51.900 --> 00:15:55.690
And nothing is sacred.

00:15:55.690 --> 00:16:00.660
This is where he lives.

00:16:00.660 --> 00:16:06.740
This is a typical drive
through a street in El Salvador.

00:16:06.740 --> 00:16:09.830
It's pretty tense.

00:16:09.830 --> 00:16:15.650
And if you go to most of the places
where there are ongoing strife,

00:16:15.650 --> 00:16:19.700
you'll find this kind of presence.

00:16:19.700 --> 00:16:22.740
These are the backs
of genocide heirs.

00:16:22.740 --> 00:16:25.180
These are the Rwandan perpetrators.

00:16:25.180 --> 00:16:31.200
Some of them who wiped out nearly
800,000 Tutsis in just 100 days

00:16:31.200 --> 00:16:35.330
with machetes, hatchets,
clubs, knives, spears.

00:16:35.330 --> 00:16:38.150
They cleansed cities, as
they said, in the countryside

00:16:38.150 --> 00:16:40.340
of what they called cockroaches.

00:16:40.340 --> 00:16:42.090
There's a lot of inflammatory
speech,

00:16:42.090 --> 00:16:48.570 position:56%
which we see at the Holocaust Museum
and elsewhere as a leading indicator

00:16:48.570 --> 00:16:52.010
of much more violent behavior.

00:16:52.010 --> 00:16:58.340
The Hutu rallying cries were laced
with hate speech spewed by leaders

00:16:58.340 --> 00:17:02.140
on the radio, in churches.

00:17:02.140 --> 00:17:06.850
This is possible distinguished as
the fastest genocide in history.

00:17:06.850 --> 00:17:10.830
Left the country with
more than 100,000 orphans

00:17:10.830 --> 00:17:13.730
and 250,000 rape victims.

00:17:13.730 --> 00:17:19.120
A traumatized population
for generations.

00:17:19.120 --> 00:17:23.680
Yes, I'm getting a wrap-up, so I'm
going to give you a few more faces.

00:17:23.680 --> 00:17:30.120
This woman was left for dead,
crawled back from one of the piles

00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:34.800
of bodies in Rwanda inside a church
where she had gone for safe haven.

00:17:34.800 --> 00:17:39.200
And the divets in her
forehead and around her skull,

00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:41.340
you can see where the
hatchet marks were.

00:17:41.340 --> 00:17:46.710
This is an example of someone
who sought refuge, a refugee.

00:17:46.710 --> 00:17:51.560
Somebody who's now living where
she came from, returned refugee.

00:17:51.560 --> 00:17:54.310
And somebody who has to
make it through her life.

00:17:54.310 --> 00:17:57.990
And you can imagine the trauma.

00:17:57.990 --> 00:18:00.580 position:56%
I'm going to wrap up with these two.

00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:03.210 position:56%
These are octogenarian eyewitnesses.

00:18:03.210 --> 00:18:07.320
These are Ukrainian
neighbors who recall 1943

00:18:07.320 --> 00:18:13.000
when the Nazi soldiers marched
through Rava Ruska with 1,500 Jews

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:17.070
into the forest just a few
miles from the Polish border.

00:18:17.070 --> 00:18:20.730
And they are recalling
this Holocaust by bullet.

00:18:20.730 --> 00:18:24.830
He was not recalling as clearly
as she would have liked him to,

00:18:24.830 --> 00:18:30.570
so she gave him a little
stimulation and she reminded him

00:18:30.570 --> 00:18:34.010
that his own family provided
the horse that carried the cart

00:18:34.010 --> 00:18:37.450
of limp bodies to the mass graves.

00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:41.700
And she said that her mother had
to supply their kitchen table

00:18:41.700 --> 00:18:47.960
to the Nazis to rest
guns and to consume food.

00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:53.500
The Nazis needed a little
snack in between their murders.

00:18:53.500 --> 00:19:00.140
Last, I will leave you with the
Buddhist nuns outside of Nanpean.

00:19:00.140 --> 00:19:04.190
These women have shaved heads
because they symbolize widowhood.

00:19:04.190 --> 00:19:10.310
Their husbands were murdered by
the Khmer Rouge and today they live

00:19:10.310 --> 00:19:12.360
in a monastery built near the site

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:15.600
of a Khmer Rouge prison
and execution ground.

00:19:15.600 --> 00:19:18.980
And as you probably know, an
international court outside

00:19:18.980 --> 00:19:21.200
of Nanpean is pursuing charges

00:19:21.200 --> 00:19:25.100
against the Khmer Rouge
founders, strategists, operatives.

00:19:25.100 --> 00:19:27.760
It's an effort towards
representative justice.

00:19:27.760 --> 00:19:30.190
They can't possibly
try all the millions

00:19:30.190 --> 00:19:34.660
of people who were perpetrators.

00:19:34.660 --> 00:19:41.020
These women, 30 years after the
genocide, these women are part

00:19:41.020 --> 00:19:44.080
of a nation where everyone
is a survivor, where victims

00:19:44.080 --> 00:19:46.590
and perpetrators live side-by-side.

00:19:46.590 --> 00:19:50.860
And where the narrative
has a lot of holes in it

00:19:50.860 --> 00:19:53.310
because there are a
lot of non-truths.

00:19:53.310 --> 00:19:57.270
But here at this former
execution ground turned monastery,

00:19:57.270 --> 00:20:00.020
the abiding belief is karma.

00:20:00.020 --> 00:20:03.050
So thank you for this
brief introduction

00:20:03.050 --> 00:20:07.510
into the beautiful conversation.

00:20:07.510 --> 00:20:12.530
