00:47:26.040 --> 00:47:29.260
Just to give you a
historical background,

00:47:29.260 --> 00:47:32.720
speaking about Greek Civil
War, it's a long story.

00:47:32.720 --> 00:47:37.810
And very often historians
are wrapping it in a way

00:47:37.810 --> 00:47:41.040
into three rounds or three circles.

00:47:41.040 --> 00:47:46.320
The one, the split within Greek
population was happening already

00:47:46.320 --> 00:47:48.020
during the second World War.

00:47:48.020 --> 00:47:52.060
And that's sometimes first drawn

00:47:52.060 --> 00:47:58.230
around where the leftists
resistance fighters were fighting

00:47:58.230 --> 00:48:04.670
against the other fighters,
closer to the republicans,

00:48:04.670 --> 00:48:09.710
or maybe best to say
anti-communist views.

00:48:09.710 --> 00:48:14.740
Once the second World War in Greece
was over, which was a bit earlier

00:48:14.740 --> 00:48:18.660
than we speak about the end of
the second World War in Europe.

00:48:18.660 --> 00:48:21.880
And it's already in autumn 1944.

00:48:21.880 --> 00:48:25.160
Very soon another round,
a so-called second round

00:48:25.160 --> 00:48:26.830
of the Greek Civil War started.

00:48:26.830 --> 00:48:29.310 position:56%
And because it happened in December,

00:48:29.310 --> 00:48:34.660
it came up in the history
as the name [inaudible].

00:48:34.660 --> 00:48:39.650
This second round, a very violent
one, took only several months.

00:48:39.650 --> 00:48:43.980
But we can still speak of a
kind of post-conflict society

00:48:43.980 --> 00:48:46.400
and about flourishing democracy

00:48:46.400 --> 00:48:49.680
after the second round
of civil war in Greece.

00:48:49.680 --> 00:48:56.530
Because very soon after, in
spring 1946, the third round

00:48:56.530 --> 00:48:59.080
of Greek Civil War started.

00:48:59.080 --> 00:49:03.810
It lasted about three
years and sometimes

00:49:03.810 --> 00:49:06.410
in literature you can read only

00:49:06.410 --> 00:49:11.130
about the so-called third
round as the civil war.

00:49:11.130 --> 00:49:16.980
That was also the timing where
many people were about to escape

00:49:16.980 --> 00:49:19.330
from Greece for various reasons.

00:49:19.330 --> 00:49:23.760
But mostly because of the fight
which was happening in Greece.

00:49:23.760 --> 00:49:28.870
If you imagine the mountainous
territory of norther Greece,

00:49:28.870 --> 00:49:33.310
these mountains and villages
were bombed and napalmed

00:49:33.310 --> 00:49:37.060
with the help of Greek
western allies.

00:49:37.060 --> 00:49:42.030
Because at that point of
course we are already speaking

00:49:42.030 --> 00:49:45.390
about a world splitting
in the east and west.

00:49:45.390 --> 00:49:50.960
So Greece became a part
of the western world,

00:49:50.960 --> 00:49:55.140
whereas those fighters in
the mountains were fighting

00:49:55.140 --> 00:50:03.100
for their ideals and for their
political beliefs of communism.

00:50:03.100 --> 00:50:05.560
And there were many of them.

00:50:05.560 --> 00:50:10.810
But speaking in terms of
the refugees, the peasants,

00:50:10.810 --> 00:50:13.580
the Greek peasants in the villages,

00:50:13.580 --> 00:50:18.960
they certainly were very afraid
not only of the political violence

00:50:18.960 --> 00:50:21.580
which was happening at
that time in Greece.

00:50:21.580 --> 00:50:25.170
But I want to remind those
of you who may not know

00:50:25.170 --> 00:50:30.960
that there were tens of thousands
of Greeks imprisoned in that period

00:50:30.960 --> 00:50:37.290
in Greek prisons and
on solitude islands.

00:50:37.290 --> 00:50:40.050
But also several thousand

00:50:40.050 --> 00:50:44.140
of them were sentenced
to death and executed.

00:50:44.140 --> 00:50:47.170
So this is a very turbulent
atmosphere

00:50:47.170 --> 00:50:51.220
in which this all is happening,
just to give you the background.

00:50:51.220 --> 00:50:59.260
These people were seeking for
their refuge in the countries

00:50:59.260 --> 00:51:00.870
which Greece is neighboring with.

00:51:00.870 --> 00:51:06.280
And as you can see, in fact all
of the countries became more

00:51:06.280 --> 00:51:10.630
or less part of what would
be called the eastern block.

00:51:10.630 --> 00:51:12.810
Of course the differences.

00:51:12.810 --> 00:51:18.520 position:56%
We can't speak of the same political
system in Albania or Yugoslavia.

00:51:18.520 --> 00:51:21.090
One different case
was Bulgaria as well.

00:51:21.090 --> 00:51:26.510
So these were mostly heading to
the north to those countries.

00:51:26.510 --> 00:51:31.110
And you can see that the
division here in 1950,

00:51:31.110 --> 00:51:38.180
the number of 76,000 refugees,
which went even higher.

00:51:38.180 --> 00:51:45.060
Most historians estimate about
100,000 people who moved only

00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:47.760
from Greece and only
within two years.

00:51:47.760 --> 00:51:54.190
You see that the number of refugees
in these years is a very big one.

00:51:54.190 --> 00:51:57.820
Most of them were heading first
to the neighboring countries,

00:51:57.820 --> 00:52:02.270
but they settled or were
moved to other countries.

00:52:02.270 --> 00:52:08.780 position:56%
And as you can see, the number of
Yugoslavia would be the highest one.

00:52:08.780 --> 00:52:13.500
It needed to be said that
this number is counting most

00:52:13.500 --> 00:52:16.510
of the Slavic-speaking
population in it.

00:52:16.510 --> 00:52:21.110
And after the Tito-Stalin
split in '48,

00:52:21.110 --> 00:52:25.710
Greeks of Greek ethnicity
were shifted

00:52:25.710 --> 00:52:28.970
under different political
circumstances

00:52:28.970 --> 00:52:31.540
to other eastern block countries.

00:52:31.540 --> 00:52:36.360
Then we have the Soviet Union,
where a lot of political elites

00:52:36.360 --> 00:52:38.820
of the Greek communist
party and some

00:52:38.820 --> 00:52:41.630
of their family members
were stationed.

00:52:41.630 --> 00:52:47.850
As for Czech Republic, which
becomes the third strongest group

00:52:47.850 --> 00:52:50.770
in this chart, they were
mostly children coming.

00:52:50.770 --> 00:52:54.860
Only within half a year,

00:52:54.860 --> 00:52:59.050
4,000 children were
pushed to Czechoslovakia.

00:52:59.050 --> 00:53:02.290
As I said, mostly Bohemia
and Moravia.

00:53:02.290 --> 00:53:04.300
And elderly people.

00:53:04.300 --> 00:53:08.860
Why? Because of the
medical care they needed.

00:53:08.860 --> 00:53:13.100
So it was decided that the
social system and medical system

00:53:13.100 --> 00:53:17.810
in Czechoslovakia is on the
level that it can absorb

00:53:17.810 --> 00:53:20.100
and help this group of population.

00:53:20.100 --> 00:53:24.640
So if we speak of the elderly
population, we are discussing now

00:53:24.640 --> 00:53:29.610
as being the most endangered
group in this time.

00:53:29.610 --> 00:53:35.260
It was a strategically
structured way to put children

00:53:35.260 --> 00:53:37.920
and where you could
put elderly people.

00:53:37.920 --> 00:53:46.020
What did happen in this time?

00:53:46.020 --> 00:53:53.220
Nearly 13,000 refugees by the
time are put in Czechoslovakia.

00:53:53.220 --> 00:53:57.720
It's very interesting to
see that they were scattered

00:53:57.720 --> 00:54:03.060
in about 24 towns and
villages around Czechoslovakia.

00:54:03.060 --> 00:54:07.230
And in a form they were
very close to each other,

00:54:07.230 --> 00:54:10.190
at least at the beginning.

00:54:10.190 --> 00:54:18.900
The main purpose to put them
in northern Moravia, this part.

00:54:18.900 --> 00:54:22.610
And I give you also
the map of Europe just

00:54:22.610 --> 00:54:26.180
to give you more general
picture of where

00:54:26.180 --> 00:54:30.770
to put Czech Republic on a map.

00:54:30.770 --> 00:54:35.270
They were put into those villages
first because they were welcomed

00:54:35.270 --> 00:54:38.180
after the explosion
of German population.

00:54:38.180 --> 00:54:42.060
But as you could see in
Michel's presentation,

00:54:42.060 --> 00:54:45.500
German population was
settled around the borders

00:54:45.500 --> 00:54:47.820
and also in some other cities.

00:54:47.820 --> 00:54:55.070
But it had to remain
secret, isolated and safe.

00:54:55.070 --> 00:55:03.240 position:56%
So if you want to push refugees in a
part of a country which is isolated,

00:55:03.240 --> 00:55:06.930
it's a mountainous area rule.

00:55:06.930 --> 00:55:13.190
Which is now without a basic, very
significant group of population.

00:55:13.190 --> 00:55:15.800
Which is safe because of
the neighboring Poland,

00:55:15.800 --> 00:55:21.810
not like Western Germany or what
became Western Germany, or Austria.

00:55:21.810 --> 00:55:24.870
Which can remain secret.

00:55:24.870 --> 00:55:29.340
The basic idea was also that
this population should work

00:55:29.340 --> 00:55:32.110
in similar conditions as
they worked in Greece,

00:55:32.110 --> 00:55:36.940
which was a peasantry
and working as farmers.

00:55:36.940 --> 00:55:41.500
But this was very soon
viewed as impossible.

00:55:41.500 --> 00:55:48.440
Because at that time the forestry
and the farms, nationalized farms

00:55:48.440 --> 00:55:54.840
in Czechoslovakia, which at
that point after the coup de tat

00:55:54.840 --> 00:55:59.600
in February '48, became a
part of the eastern block.

00:55:59.600 --> 00:56:02.910
Those are very much industrialized

00:56:02.910 --> 00:56:07.300
and had a very good industrial
base already from the 19th century.

00:56:07.300 --> 00:56:13.170
So very soon the refugees realize
that they can earn a better living

00:56:13.170 --> 00:56:17.680
if they go to the industrial
centers, which were in some

00:56:17.680 --> 00:56:23.620
of the major towns in this
district which was also in Brno.

00:56:23.620 --> 00:56:25.510
So you can see this spot here.

00:56:25.510 --> 00:56:29.580
And later on, especially as
they started their education

00:56:29.580 --> 00:56:31.910
at universities, et cetera.

00:56:31.910 --> 00:56:37.400
Many of them moved to
the capital of Prague.

00:56:37.400 --> 00:56:42.060
We can see at this point
that the integration

00:56:42.060 --> 00:56:46.880
of the refugees wasn't really
a straightforward process.

00:56:46.880 --> 00:56:50.150
And that's what can connect
us with today's situation.

00:56:50.150 --> 00:56:52.780
It's not a straightforward process.

00:56:52.780 --> 00:56:55.750
It was rather a gradual process

00:56:55.750 --> 00:56:57.860
which took several years
and many decisions.

00:56:57.860 --> 00:57:00.040
And you have to see the loyalties

00:57:00.040 --> 00:57:04.790
of the Greek communist party,
which was exterminated.

00:57:04.790 --> 00:57:09.850
Because in Greece it was
already forbidden ever since 1947

00:57:09.850 --> 00:57:16.380
and remained forbidden until
the fall of Greek Junta in '74.

00:57:16.380 --> 00:57:23.210
So all this period in Greek history
used to be called, and in Greek law

00:57:23.210 --> 00:57:28.890
as well, used to be called the
period of the permanent civil war.

00:57:28.890 --> 00:57:34.960
So imagine that even in the
fixed Cold War you have a country

00:57:34.960 --> 00:57:38.180
in the south of Europe and
you could certainly compare it

00:57:38.180 --> 00:57:40.900
with Spain or with Portugal.

00:57:40.900 --> 00:57:44.560
You have a country where
you have permanent Civil War

00:57:44.560 --> 00:57:48.600
with legal instruments up to '74.

00:57:48.600 --> 00:57:56.470
And we have to keep that in mind
when thinking about this division.

00:57:56.470 --> 00:58:04.030
So once the refugees
arrive to Czechoslovakia,

00:58:04.030 --> 00:58:07.560
I already mentioned
it wasn't an easy way.

00:58:07.560 --> 00:58:13.930
It was a very nice experience
lecturing at one of the schools

00:58:13.930 --> 00:58:19.350
in the Czech Republic where I was
giving a similar lecture to kids

00:58:19.350 --> 00:58:21.120
who were about 10 years old.

00:58:21.120 --> 00:58:26.330 position:56%
And they had the idea and these
kids were surely travelling by train

00:58:26.330 --> 00:58:29.090
or by cars or even by airplanes.

00:58:29.090 --> 00:58:31.000
No, they went on foot.

00:58:31.000 --> 00:58:32.730
So they were crossing the border

00:58:32.730 --> 00:58:36.670
on foot towards Albania
and towards Bulgaria.

00:58:36.670 --> 00:58:41.160
And from over there, they ended
up going through the Dardanelles

00:58:41.160 --> 00:58:45.350
and through Black Sea
to Soviet Union.

00:58:45.350 --> 00:58:49.150
Or they made crossing
through the Mediterranean Sea

00:58:49.150 --> 00:58:52.600
through to Gibraltar,
around Great Britain

00:58:52.600 --> 00:58:55.390
where sometimes the ships
were heavily attacked.

00:58:55.390 --> 00:59:01.750
Up to Poland, to Gdansk and then
through Poland to Czechoslovakia.

00:59:01.750 --> 00:59:06.460
So you can see the many
trajectories where the blue files,

00:59:06.460 --> 00:59:09.780
the yellow files, and that
would be this direction.

00:59:09.780 --> 00:59:14.150
Then from Yugoslavia they
were exposed then to Hungary

00:59:14.150 --> 00:59:18.300
and later came some of
them to Czechoslovakia.

00:59:18.300 --> 00:59:22.860
The other darts we can see here,
that's another difficult story.

00:59:22.860 --> 00:59:28.630
Because many of the families ended
up divided in different countries.

00:59:28.630 --> 00:59:33.220
And it took one more decade
to reunite the families.

00:59:33.220 --> 00:59:36.030
So you have to imagine
children, some children,

00:59:36.030 --> 00:59:39.350
living in children's homes
because they were not orphans.

00:59:39.350 --> 00:59:41.950
It was not an orphanage.

00:59:41.950 --> 00:59:44.680
Without their parents, being
in a different country.

00:59:44.680 --> 00:59:49.450
Or maybe being in the very same
country, but they were deprived,

00:59:49.450 --> 00:59:52.470
all of them, all who
came to Czechoslovakia,

00:59:52.470 --> 00:59:57.740
to stay with their families
until they reached the age of 14

00:59:57.740 --> 01:00:02.890
when they started studies
or started to work.

01:00:02.890 --> 01:00:08.800
So they were institutionalized,
compulsory in these student homes.

01:00:08.800 --> 01:00:12.390
Where they were experiencing
a double education

01:00:12.390 --> 01:00:15.570
and in fact a double
indoctrination as well

01:00:15.570 --> 01:00:20.510
from the Czech communist party and
an education from Czech teachers.

01:00:20.510 --> 01:00:25.540
But also the Greek communist
party and the education

01:00:25.540 --> 01:00:29.530
of the very same thing
from the Greek teachers

01:00:29.530 --> 01:00:32.610
or Slavic-speaking
teachers from Greece.

01:00:32.610 --> 01:00:36.210
So you can see that this
patchwork was working

01:00:36.210 --> 01:00:42.350
and that the state agreed
through Soviet Union and Moscow

01:00:42.350 --> 01:00:45.710
with Greek communist party and
Czechoslovak communist party

01:00:45.710 --> 01:00:50.980
in educating those refugees
in both of the languages.

01:00:50.980 --> 01:00:52.280
What happened?

01:00:52.280 --> 01:00:59.350
They achieved to make a very
strong feeling of patriotism.

01:00:59.350 --> 01:01:02.580
They made them bilingual,
all of them.

01:01:02.580 --> 01:01:06.550
And they made them to know
histories of both of the countries,

01:01:06.550 --> 01:01:09.960
even if of course shaped in a way

01:01:09.960 --> 01:01:12.730
as history was shaped
during the Cold War.

01:01:12.730 --> 01:01:19.790
But it seems that this process was
a very successful one because most

01:01:19.790 --> 01:01:24.780
of the children, and we don't
have a psychologist telling them,

01:01:24.780 --> 01:01:28.060
very good results usually
with children who went

01:01:28.060 --> 01:01:30.250
through orphanages
or children's homes.

01:01:30.250 --> 01:01:35.660
These children were able to
create their own families,

01:01:35.660 --> 01:01:38.900
were very successful
in their new positions.

01:01:38.900 --> 01:01:42.750
And most of them, at least the
statistics are saying 80% of them,

01:01:42.750 --> 01:01:47.680
finished their university degree,
mostly in technical schools,

01:01:47.680 --> 01:01:50.940
medical schools or
pedagogic schools.

01:01:50.940 --> 01:01:55.780
Of course the policy
was playing with that.

01:01:55.780 --> 01:02:01.140
But I just want to give you a basic
picture of what was happening.

01:02:01.140 --> 01:02:05.190
The composition, as I already
mentioned, in Czechoslovakia,

01:02:05.190 --> 01:02:07.310
was as you see on the chart.

01:02:07.310 --> 01:02:14.090
And I would only like to
highlight some of the usual myths.

01:02:14.090 --> 01:02:18.390
And one of the myths is
that it was only communists

01:02:18.390 --> 01:02:20.490
who were coming to those countries.

01:02:20.490 --> 01:02:27.330
So if you have the number of 13,000
refugees coming to Czechoslovakia,

01:02:27.330 --> 01:02:33.780
only 1,000-2,000 of them,
depending on the time period,

01:02:33.780 --> 01:02:36.060 position:56%
were members of the communist party.

01:02:36.060 --> 01:02:39.220 position:56%
And later on of course there was the
growing of the second generation,

01:02:39.220 --> 01:02:42.720
which also counts into
these 1,000-2,000 members

01:02:42.720 --> 01:02:44.390
of communist party.

01:02:44.390 --> 01:02:49.980
The other one is the composition
of Greeks and Slavophones

01:02:49.980 --> 01:02:56.950
or Slavomacedonians, but also other
small groups who defined themselves

01:02:56.950 --> 01:02:59.630
as Turks or Armans or kind

01:02:59.630 --> 01:03:04.270
of Romanian-speaking
population of Greece.

01:03:04.270 --> 01:03:08.420
And as I already mentioned,
many of them brought children

01:03:08.420 --> 01:03:11.930
and youngsters under the age of 13.

01:03:11.930 --> 01:03:14.260
Which of course leads to the fact

01:03:14.260 --> 01:03:18.250
that from this group only a
very small number was able

01:03:18.250 --> 01:03:20.670
to work immediately
because they were not

01:03:20.670 --> 01:03:23.080
at the age of being sent to work.

01:03:23.080 --> 01:03:27.070
And Czechoslovakia was
trying to educate them first.

01:03:27.070 --> 01:03:31.760
And then we have those
elderly people how are send

01:03:31.760 --> 01:03:35.700
to health institutions
and being helped socially.

01:03:35.700 --> 01:03:40.340
So the social program
around all this emigration

01:03:40.340 --> 01:03:46.540 position:56%
and about all this emigration was a
very expensive one for 13,000 people

01:03:46.540 --> 01:03:49.230
in only about three year's period.

01:03:49.230 --> 01:04:00.460 position:56%
You can see that the ripple creation
took a long time and it can erupt

01:04:00.460 --> 01:04:03.790
in all the periods of the Cold War.

01:04:03.790 --> 01:04:11.130
So the first group went
back to Greece in fall '54,

01:04:11.130 --> 01:04:17.980 position:56%
which was the time after the death
of Stalin, where the first agreement

01:04:17.980 --> 01:04:21.640
between Greece and
Czechoslovakia was signed.

01:04:21.640 --> 01:04:25.080
After that, you could
apply only individually.

01:04:25.080 --> 01:04:30.780
And if you see that the numbers
are dropping very significantly,

01:04:30.780 --> 01:04:37.250 position:56%
in the '60's when the policy changed
once again and became more relaxed,

01:04:37.250 --> 01:04:40.040 position:56%
bigger number of people is going in.

01:04:40.040 --> 01:04:44.190
We have here the Greek Junta
where nearly nobody was going back

01:04:44.190 --> 01:04:48.470 position:56%
because of course people were
scared of persecution back in Greece

01:04:48.470 --> 01:04:50.610
and they had reason for that.

01:04:50.610 --> 01:04:59.870
After the laws in '74 and later
on in '80-81, with the new rule

01:04:59.870 --> 01:05:08.310
of the socialist party of Greece,
[inaudible], many refugees decided

01:05:08.310 --> 01:05:13.670
to return back because of
the rules which were issued.

01:05:13.670 --> 01:05:19.410
Which outlawed the possibility
to punish them for taking place

01:05:19.410 --> 01:05:22.330
in a Greek Civil War resistance.

01:05:22.330 --> 01:05:26.870
Just to wrap up, we still do have

01:05:26.870 --> 01:05:32.340
about 3,000 Greeks
living in Czechoslovakia.

01:05:32.340 --> 01:05:38.090
And what is very significant is the
positive picture they are making

01:05:38.090 --> 01:05:39.520
in Czech society.

01:05:39.520 --> 01:05:42.150
Greece of course, as with
many other countries,

01:05:42.150 --> 01:05:46.480
became the destination
of summer holidays.

01:05:46.480 --> 01:05:51.270
But it also is renowned for
its ancient history, et cetera.

01:05:51.270 --> 01:05:53.140
But also in a country itself,

01:05:53.140 --> 01:05:58.500
it's the former Greek Civil War
refugees running Greek restaurants,

01:05:58.500 --> 01:06:03.880
having Greek shops,
who are now the aim

01:06:03.880 --> 01:06:06.910
of the visit of the
Czech population.

01:06:06.910 --> 01:06:10.500
Greek dancing groups do have
more Czechs that are dancing

01:06:10.500 --> 01:06:12.990
in them than Greeks today.

01:06:12.990 --> 01:06:19.240
So you can see the intermingling of
these groups was very significant

01:06:19.240 --> 01:06:23.570
and didn't really need to
assimilate the population

01:06:23.570 --> 01:06:26.010
which is so often discussed.

01:06:26.010 --> 01:06:30.980
If a country will accept refugees,
do we assimilate them successfully?

01:06:30.980 --> 01:06:36.760
And I do claim the success is to
live with them successfully and not

01:06:36.760 --> 01:06:39.920
to assimilate them, because
we all can gain from that.

01:06:39.920 --> 01:06:46.050
It doesn't matter if they have
a Czech national identity,

01:06:46.050 --> 01:06:53.180
as you can see, or a Stephanos who
is claiming that he was born Greek

01:06:53.180 --> 01:06:56.850
and he will die Greek even if
he never, ever travelled again

01:06:56.850 --> 01:07:00.860
to Greece after he
came to Czechoslovakia.

01:07:00.860 --> 01:07:02.540
And it's not a big distance.

01:07:02.540 --> 01:07:06.250
It's two hours by plane and
it's not that expensive either.

01:07:06.250 --> 01:07:10.150
But he doesn't want to
destroy his picture of Greece.

01:07:10.150 --> 01:07:13.600
He wants to remain
Greek in Czechoslovakia.

01:07:13.600 --> 01:07:19.350
And this is in my opinion
the message we have to spread

01:07:19.350 --> 01:07:21.580
to today's society as well.

01:07:21.580 --> 01:07:27.880 position:56%
If you have the chance to read in
Czech or Greek, you will get a story

01:07:27.880 --> 01:07:31.620
of all of those, their
identities, their political views,

01:07:31.620 --> 01:07:35.610
their life in Czechoslovakia,
either in Greek or in Czech.

01:07:35.610 --> 01:07:40.240
Unfortunately not in English, but I
hope to sum it up one day at least

01:07:40.240 --> 01:07:44.280
in an article that you can
have for all of you on that.

01:07:44.280 --> 01:07:46.510
Thank you very much
for your attention.

